race.description: Orange Motor Group Country Boosted Handicap
race.comment: Competitive. VIOLET AND BLUE (2) led and scored last start at Leeton as favourite. Rates well and keeps the handy 4kg claim. Will be fitter again and maps for a soft run. Can keep the ball rolling. TALIHINA SKY (5) resumes for the Williams yard with a 4kg claimer engaged. Proven fresh and is up to this if presented on song. She's trialled well and the late betting will be key. OBSESSIVE NATURE (1) brings improving form from the non-TABS and won his latest comfortably at Grenfell as a short-priced favourite. Draws low and keeps the 4kg claim. Stepping up a level this time, but on current form he can't be ruled out. MR BINGO (6) is well off his best but will be fitter and may fill the next slot.
